SIMPLE: toothing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toothing
<hw>Tooth"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
indenting or furnishing with teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Masonry)</fld> <def>Bricks alternately projecting
at the end of a wall, in order that they may be bonded into a
continuation of it when the remainder is carried up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Toothing plane</b></col>, <cd>a plane of which the iron
is formed into a series of small teeth, for the purpose of roughening
surfaces, as of veneers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toothless</ent>⟦br⟧
